  "steps": [
    {
      "name": "",
      "steps": [
        {
          "text": "Prepare the vegetables. **Onion:** peel, halve, and cut into medium dice. **Zucchini:** cut the ends, halve lengthwise, and cut into 1/4 cm half-moons. **Bell pepper:** remove the seeds, and cut into medium strips. **Kimchi:** roughly chop. **Pickled cucumbers:** halve.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Heat a medium-sized pot on medium-low heat, add olive oil, add onions and sauté them until golden. Add salt in the middle.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Season with a few black peppercorns, curcuma powder, and smoked paprika powder. Thoroughly mix everything, and cook for about 30 seconds.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add the zucchini, bell peppers, kimchi, and pickled cucumbers to the pot, and cook until the zucchini softens a bit.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add the chicken broth, and water, increase the heat to medium-high, bring to a boil, reduce the heat to medium-low, and cook covered for about 20 minutes, until the vegetables are tender.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add a bit of kimchi paste if not spicy enough, and more salt if needed.",
          "pause": false
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
